      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt. Stir in the old-fashioned rolled oats and set aside.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat the butter and both sugars in a stand mixer (paddle) or with a hand mixer for 1 to 2 minutes. Add the egg and vanilla. Mix until smooth, scraping down the bowl as needed.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the dry ingredients and continue mixing on low speed until just combined, then mix in the raisins.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cover the cookie dough tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Line two large baking sheets with parchment paper or silicone baking mats and set aside.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Once the dough is chilled, remove it from the refrigerator. Using a 1.5 tablespoon cookie scoop, scoop the cookie dough and drop onto the prepared baking sheets. Roll the cookie dough into balls and very gently press down with your hand to flatten each ball of cookie dough slightly. Make sure to leave a little room between each ball of cookie dough as they will spread a little while they bake.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the edges of the cookies are lightly golden brown and the tops are set. Remove from the oven and cool on the baking sheets for 5 minutes, then transfer the cookies to a wire rack to cool completely.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "NOTES",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Storage Instructions: Cookies may be stored in an airtight container at room temperature for up to one week.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Freezing Instructions: Baked cookies will freeze well for up to 3 months, thaw to room temperature before serving.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking. Preheat the oven properly, 180°C means 180°C on an oven thermometer, not the dial.",
              "cause": "Butter too soft, or oven not hot enough.",
              "symptom": "Cookies spread too thin and crisp"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stop mixing as soon as the flour disappears. For chewier cookies, replace some plain flour with bread flour for more gluten.",
              "cause": "Over-mixed once the flour went in, or too much flour.",
              "symptom": "Cookies came out cakey, not chewy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Leave them on the tray for five minutes after baking. They're too soft to move when hot. Lift onto a rack with a palette knife.",
              "cause": "Tried to lift before they'd set.",
              "symptom": "Cookies stuck to the tray"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use a heavier baking tray, line with baking paper, and bake on the middle shelf.",
              "cause": "Tray too thin, or rack too low.",
              "symptom": "Burnt bottoms, raw middles"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add-ins: 75 g dark chocolate chips, chopped walnuts, dried cranberries, or a pinch of sea salt on top before baking.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Gluten-free: replace plain flour with a 1-to-1 gluten-free blend that includes xanthan gum.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Designed as a make-ahead: assemble the night before, eat in the morning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A classic American home recipe, generous, comforting, made for a crowd. The proportions are heartier than the British equivalent; the method is built for a Sunday afternoon.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
